D) Substring 
===============



— In the Below Example we have entered the String as Hello World so they are In total 11 Characters Including space [7,5 Means Hello is 5 words and space is 6th word] So it will give us the from 7th Character & It will give 5 Characters 
In this case it has given World which is of 5 Characters


SELECT SUBSTRING('Hello World', 7,5);


+-------------------------------+
| SUBSTRING('Hello World', 7,5) |
+-------------------------------+
| World                         |
+-------------------------------+








— We can Also Give the Starting Number so it will start from that and give the result till the end [In the Below Eg we have given 3 and l is the 3rd Char and it has provided the Output till end]


SELECT SUBSTRING('Hello World', 3);


+-----------------------------+
| SUBSTRING('Hello World', 3) |
+-----------------------------+
| llo World                   |
+-----------------------------+










— -5 Matlab sirf World print krega


SELECT SUBSTRING('Hello World', -5);


+------------------------------+
| SUBSTRING('Hello World', -5) |
+------------------------------+
| World                        |
+------------------------------+








